# React & Next.js Patterns

## Server vs Client

- Server Components by default. Only add `'use client'` when the component needs browser APIs, event handlers, or hooks.
- Never fetch data in client components. Lift data fetching to Server Components or route handlers.
- Keep client components small and leaf-level.

## Component Structure

Order within a component file:

1. Imports
2. Types/interfaces specific to this component
3. Component function
4. Helper functions (non-exported)

One component per file. Co-locate sub-components only if they are tightly coupled and not reused.

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS only. No inline `style` props, no CSS modules.
- Use `cn()` utility (from `@/lib/utils`) for conditional class merging.
- Design tokens come from Tailwind config — do not hardcode colors or spacing values.

## Data Fetching

- Use `async` Server Components for data loading.
- Wrap async data sections in `<Suspense>` with meaningful fallbacks.
- Use `Promise.all()` for parallel independent fetches.
- Cache with `React.cache()` for per-request deduplication.

## Forms

- Use Server Actions with `useActionState` for form handling.
- Validate inputs server-side with Zod before processing.
- Return structured results from actions, not redirects (unless appropriate).

## Performance

- Use `next/dynamic` for heavy client components not needed on initial render.
- Images via `next/image` — always specify `width`, `height`, or `fill`.
- No anonymous functions in JSX props of memoized components.
